# ============================================================
# H-bond plotting script for Desmond MD analysis
# Author: Sang Hoon Um
#
# Purpose
#   This script reads all H-bond .csv files from one analysis folder and
#   generates publication-style time-series plots for:
#     Figure 1: Total H-bonds
#     Figure 3: Intra-chain vs inter-chain H-bonds
#     Figure 4: Inter-chain pair H-bonds (A-B, A-C, B-C)
#     Figure 5: Intra-chain H-bonds (A, B, C)
#     Figure 6: Inter-chain / total H-bond ratio
#
#   For each figure, the script saves:
#     - a faceted plot showing individual replicates and mean traces
#     - a mean-only plot
#
#   Special behavior for Figures 3, 4, and 5:
#     - If only one structure/variant is present, the mean-only plot keeps the
#       original single-panel style.
#     - If multiple structures/variants are present, the mean-only plot
#       automatically switches to a faceted panel layout. This keeps the
#       category comparisons readable while avoiding crowded multi-line plots.
#
# Expected input folder
#   ~/Desktop/md_simulation/Hbond/<target_folder>/
#
# Expected input filename format
#   YYYY-MM-DD_MAINSTRUCTURE[_SUBTYPE]_rX_Hbond.csv
#
# Examples
#   2026-04-27_NPG6-4_r1_Hbond.csv
#   2026-04-27_NPG6-4_A0a_r1_Hbond.csv
#
# Expected CSV columns
#   frame, all, intra_A, intra_B, intra_C, inter_AB, inter_AC, inter_BC
#
# Metadata parsing rule
#   - The first field is treated as the date.
#   - The field matching r1, r2, r3, ... is treated as the replicate ID.
#   - The first field between date and replicate is the main structure.
#       Example: NPG6-4
#   - Any additional field between main structure and replicate is treated
#     as a subtype / pattern label.
#       Example: A0a
#
# Notes on color handling
#   - Variant colors are assigned automatically unless manual_colors is set.
#   - H-bond class colors and chain-pair colors can also be manually edited
#     in the user settings section.
# ============================================================

